The President has authorized the U.S. Armed Forces to conduct targeted airstrikes in Iraq in order to protect American personnel and help forces in Iraq fight against the terrorist group Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant. The military operations will be limited in scope and duration. The President has also authorized humanitarian assistance in Iraq to support the civilians trapped on Mount Sinjar. These actions are being taken in coordination with the Iraqi government and are in the national security and foreign policy interests of the United States. The President is providing this report to keep Congress informed, in accordance with the War Powers Resolution.